# AGENTS.md

This file is the repo entry point for Codex and other coding agents.

Keep context lean. Treat this file as a router, not as the full system of
record. Read only the docs that are relevant to the task you are doing.

## Core Rule

- Do not load every document in `docs/` by default.
- Start from the smallest useful context.
- Follow links to deeper docs only when the task clearly touches that area.
- If a deeper `AGENTS.md` is added later inside a subdirectory, it overrides
  this file for that subtree.

## Repo Map

- `README.md`: repo overview, local development, and general workflow.
- `apps/webapp`: Vite + React + Relay frontend.
- `apps/server`: NestJS + GraphQL + TypeORM backend.
- `deploy/cloudflare-pages`: frontend deployment module and scripts.
- `deploy/cloudrun`: backend deployment module and scripts.
- `docs/ai/INDEX.md`: index of AI-facing repo rules and selective-loading docs.

## Selective Doc Loading

- Read `README.md` first for general repo orientation.
- Read `docs/ai/INDEX.md` when the task involves repo conventions, AI-facing
  rules, or when you need help deciding which deeper doc to load.
- Read subsystem docs only when working in that subsystem.
- Prefer the closest, most specific source of truth over broader background
  docs.

## When To Read Bash Module Guidance

Read `docs/ai/INDEX.md`, then `docs/BASH_MODULE.md`, when the task involves any
of the following:

- Editing shell scripts or bash-based automation.
- Editing `deploy/**/scripts/*`.
- Editing bash-based validation under `deploy/**/tests/*`.
- Reorganizing a bash-heavy module directory.
- Introducing or changing `config/.env`, `.env.example`, `.env.local`,
  `scripts/load-env.sh`, or `scripts/lib/paths.sh`.
- Defining path helper variables for scripts that may be sourced by other
  scripts.

When that guidance is in scope:

- Resolve module paths from each script's own location, not from the current
  working directory.
- Prefer one env-loading entry point per bash module.
- Use collision-safe exported variable names for reusable sourced helpers.

## Area-Specific Routing

- For frontend app work in `apps/webapp`, use local package scripts and keep
  Relay artifacts in sync when GraphQL query shapes change.
- For backend app work in `apps/server`, use local package scripts and relevant
  tests.
- For backend deployment work in `deploy/cloudrun`, start with
  `deploy/cloudrun/README.md`, then load only the needed docs from
  `deploy/cloudrun/docs/`.
- For frontend deployment work in `deploy/cloudflare-pages`, start with
  `deploy/cloudflare-pages/README.md`, then load only the needed docs from
  `deploy/cloudflare-pages/docs/`.

## Working Style

- Prefer targeted, minimal edits that preserve the current monorepo structure.
- Keep new documentation close to the subsystem it describes.
- Add links to deeper docs instead of duplicating long guidance in this file.
- If a rule becomes important across repeated tasks, update `docs/ai/INDEX.md`
  to route to it rather than growing this file into a large manual.

If a change is documentation-only but makes concrete claims about commands,
paths, or layout, run the lightest relevant verification you can.
